cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network congestion control experiments with QUIC on Rapla, Tapa, and Valga
  nodes under varying latency and bandwidth conditions
abstract: This dataset captures network congestion control performance evaluations
  using QUIC protocol implementations across three distributed nodes. Experiments
  apply controlled latency, bandwidth constraints, and scheduling policies to assess
  protocol behavior under simulated network stress. Each node configures dual-interface
  topologies with traffic shaping, executing 10 iterations per configuration to measure
  energy consumption, throughput, and latency. Results include per-run logs, network
  trace captures, and visualization outputs for analyzing algorithm performance under
  constrained conditions.
